	abstract = {Modern cloud-native systems based on Kubernetes and microservices architectures generate massive volumes of telemetry data that challenge traditional anomaly detection approaches. While existing tools can identify potential issues, they fail to provide contextual explanations, resulting in prolonged incident resolution times and compliance challenges in regulated industries. This paper introduces a novel framework that combines Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with vector similarity search to deliver explainable anomaly detection for distributed systems. The approach retrieves relevant historical incidents using semantic embeddings, then generates humanreadable diagnostic explanations through large language models. Additionally, the framework incorporates compliance-aware audit mechanisms to satisfy regulatory requirements including GDPR, SOC 2, and HIPAA. Experimental evaluation on a realistic enterprise microservices deployment demonstrates a 42% reduction in mean time to resolution, 76% F1-score for anomaly detection, and 39% reduction in false positives. The system achieves 78% accuracy in technical explanation correctness and 89% compliance audit readiness, addressing critical operational and regulatory challenges in cloud-native environments. © 2025 IEEE.},
