	abstract = {Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) has gained prominence for developing chatbots interacting with document repositories, yet substantial empirical evidence indicates critical failures due to inherent vector search limitations, context fragmentation from chunking, and high maintenance complexity. This paper provides an original contribution by rigorously analyzing these practical challenges and proposing a robust alternative leveraging structured metadata and Large Language Models (LLMs). Unlike conventional RAG systems, our approach utilizes metadata-driven retrieval combined with Context-Aware Generation (CAG) in a hybrid architecture, significantly enhancing scalability, accuracy, and maintainability. We introduce a mathematical evaluation framework and concrete recommendations, demonstrating superior performance and efficiency through systematic benchmarking. © 2025 IEEE.},
