	abstract = {In today's data-driven world, traditional BI platforms fall short in providing real-time, context-aware insights. Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT-3 and LLaMA excel in natural language tasks but struggle with outdated knowledge and hallucinations. Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) bridges this gap by integrating LLMs with external data sources such as databases, APIs, or vector stores. This chapter explores RAG's architecture, combining retrievers (e.g., FAISS, Elasticsearch) with generators (e.g., GPT, Claude) and its enterprise applications in finance, marketing, HR, and supply chain. Key challenges like data governance, latency, and ethical considerations are discussed, offering a roadmap for deploying RAG to enhance real-time decision-making. Copyright © 2026, IGI Global Scientific Publishing. Copying or distributing in print or electronic forms without written permission of IGI Global Scientific Publishing is prohibited. Use of this chapter to train generative artificial intelligence (AI) technologies is expressly prohibited. The publisher reserves all rights to license its use for generative AI training and machine learning model development.},
