	abstract = {Large language model based artificial intelligence(AI) Agent provides new paths for intelligent enterprise office workflows relying on their advantages of intent recognition and tool invocation. Three representative enterprise scenarios are selected, including financial invoice reimbursement, contract compliance review, and institutional question-answering. This paper proposes and designs an integrated enterprise intelligent system. The system adopts a multi-agent modular architecture: the financial invoice reimbursement agent realizes information extraction and missing detection based on the prompt engineering large language agent, the contract compliance review agent improves risk identification capabilities with fine-tuning BERT+knowledge graph embedding, the institutional question-answering agent realizes cross-modal query based on the Retrieval-Augmented Generation(RAG) mechanism. Following the comparative evaluation and validation of mainstream models, the proposed system demonstrates robust performance across key tasks, which includes an F1-score of 84% in financial information extraction, an accuracy of 90% in missing information detection, an F1-score of 85% in contract risk identification, a detection rate of 82.3% for implicit risks, and an accuracy of 83% in institutional question answering. The system is highly responsive, reducing labor costs and providing intelligent support for enterprise digital transformation.  © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
