	abstract = {In large-scale enterprise software systems, iden-tifying performance issues and application faults remains a time-consuming task, often relying on manual analysis of logs, code, and telemetry. This paper presents a novel RAG-based Code Intelligence Framework that integrates large language models (LLMs) with Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to automate and contextualize fault diagnosis in real time. By combining static code analysis, dynamic logs, and performance test data with a vectorized document store, the framework retrieves relevant artifacts and generates natural language expla-nations for detected anomalies. The approach is validated using three comprehensive case studies across FinTech, HealthTech, and e-commerce domains, along with controlled experiments on synthetic enterprise data. Experimental results show a 62% reduction in mean time to resolution (MTTR), 89% diagnostic accuracy, and significantly increased developer trust through explainable root cause suggestions.  © 2025 IEEE.},
