	affiliations = {Vishwakarma Institute of Information Technology, Dept. of CSE-AI, Pune, India; Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Dept. of CSE-AI, Pune, India; Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Dept. of CSE-AIML, Pune, India; Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Dept. of Computer Engineering, Pune, India},
	abstract = {This research introduces Gideon, a new AI assistant for finance and accounting that works within the Odoo ERP environment. The tool has been developed in an effort to overcome long-standing operational inefficiencies in financial processes, such as delays in month-end closing, laborious manual reconciliations, and manual compliance monitoring. By embedding advanced Large Language Models (LLMs), our AI assistant offers an intelligent and contextualized support role that enhances the use of human-supervised workflows and (project) customized processes within existing practices. Features include: AI-driven expense analysis to provide real-time insights about spending habits, document conversation querying using a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline, and automatic mapping of unstructured documents into the ERP. The system was developed using a Docker-based modular and containerized architecture with Odoo 18, PostgreSQL 13, and an on-premise Ollama instance running the Llama 38 B model for data privacy. The performance evaluation showed that we had made drastic operational improvements 95% success rate in document text extraction, 88% accuracy in query intent classification, and overall faster time-to-insight for complex financial analysis. The system is compliant and governed in that it makes use of Odoo's role-based access controls and immutable logging, guaranteeing all AI-related actions on the platform are part of an audit trail and secure. This study discusses a practical and scalable example of a control aware AI assistant that improves productivity, democratizes access to financial data, and enables finance professionals to spend their time on strategic valuation tasks that create the most value. © 2025 IEEE.},
