	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105035607133?origin=resultslist},
	affiliations = {Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Pune, India; E-Zest Solutions Ltd, Pune, India},
	abstract = {This research introduces an advanced intelligent IT support chatbot framework that revolutionizes traditional helpdesk operations through the integration of cutting-edge natural language processing technologies and scalable vector search methodologies. The system addresses critical challenges in enterprise IT support environments, including prolonged response times, inconsistent solution quality, and escalating operational expenditures associated with manual ticket resolution processes. The proposed architecture employs a fine-tuned Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) model for sophisticated multi-intent classification and semantic embedding generation of user queries and historical ticket databases. A high-performance Pinecone vector database facilitates rapid similarity-based retrieval through optimized cosine distance calculations, enabling contextually relevant historical issue identification within milliseconds. The system incorporates a domain-specialized Large Language Model for Advanced Reasoning (LLaMA) implementation that generates human-aligned, contextually appropriate responses using retrieval-augmented generation techniques. Key innovations include a privacy-preserving federated learning architecture enabling collaborative model enhancement across organizational boundaries without compromising sensitive enterprise data, integrated JIRA workflow automation for seamless ticket lifecycle management, and an intelligent uncertainty estimation mechanism providing reliable fallback protocols through human-in-the-loop interventions. Comprehensive evaluation demonstrates exceptional performance metrics: 93.2% intent classification accuracy, 180-millisecond average response latency, and 88.6% user satisfaction rates while automating 50% of routine queries with enterprise-grade security standards, representing a significant advancement in intelligent service desk automation technologies for large-scale organizational deployments. © 2025 IEEE.},
	author_keywords = {BERT; Chatbot; Federated Learning; IT Support Automation; LLaMA; NLP; Pinecone; Ticket Resolution; Transformer; Vector Search},
