	affiliations = {PES University, Department of Computer Science & Engineering, Bangalore, India},
	abstract = {This work proposes an extremely scalable Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) platform running on Kubernetes on the Amazon Web Services (AWS) for document knowledge. It uses AWS AI services, Amazon Bedrock, OpenSearch, EC2, and S3 to securely fetch documents, chunk the semantics, and generate LLM-based responses. Microservices architecture and cloud-native design make the system automatically scale, tolerant, and highly available. CI/CD pipeline automates deployment and updates for real-time efficiency and agility. Furthermore, the system supports multilingual documents and extracts knowledge from complex enterprise documents. The users can upload, process, and analyze various documents for intelligent and in-depth querying. Dynamic retrieval pipelines will be orchestrated over the scalable infrastructure to maximize the RAG potential in the cloud. An end-to-end product for real-world enterprise applications will demonstrate that sophisticated document analysis and understanding would be complemented by an end-to-end toolset that is high-performance, secure, and robust, demonstrating pragmatic capability behind current cloud-native AI. © 2025 IEEE.},
